        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 6:55PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 654 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 13 miles northwest of Hoffman to near
Rockingham to near Hamlet. Movement was northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, pea size hail, and torrential
rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southern Pines, Rockingham, Carthage, Pinehurst, Hamlet, Aberdeen,
Biscoe, Hoffman, Pinebluff, and Ellerbe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
